@startuml Bug 6.4 — Call-flow diagram (Vocabulary lesson list load & render)
!theme plain
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam maxMessageSize 160

' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
' Use case — App start-up: lesson data loaded and rendered in LessonStackList
' ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
== Use Case: App start-up — lesson list loaded and reactively rendered ==

participant "main()\n(src/main.rs)" as Main
participant "vocabulary::init\n(lib/vocabulary/src/lib.rs ~L160)" as VocabInit
participant "load_vocabulary() /\nload_and_save_defaults()\n(lib/vocabulary/src/lib.rs ~L113, ~L142)\n#cfg desktop: std::fs::read_to_string\n#cfg wasm32: include_str! seed JSON only" as Loader
participant "lessons_to_slint()\n(lib/vocabulary/src/lib.rs ~L71)" as Convert
participant "VocabularyAppLogic\n(global, lib/vocabulary)\nlesson-list: [VocabularyLessonModel]" as VocabLogic
participant "LessonStackList\n(Slint UI,\nlib/vocabulary/ui/components)" as LessonUI

Main -> VocabInit : vocabulary::init(&window)

alt vocabulary.json does not exist (first run)
    VocabInit -> Loader : load_and_save_defaults()
    Loader -> Loader : include_str!(n5_verbs.json,\nn5_adjectives.json, n5_vocabulary.json)\n→ parse → save_vocabulary() writes vocabulary.json
    Loader --> VocabInit : Vec<LessonData> (defaults, ~18 lessons)
else vocabulary.json exists
    VocabInit -> Loader : load_vocabulary()
    Loader -> Loader : std::fs::read_to_string(VOCABULARY_FILE)\n→ serde_json::from_str::<Vec<LessonData>>
    Loader --> VocabInit : Vec<LessonData> (persisted lessons)
end

VocabInit -> Convert : lessons_to_slint(&lessons)
Convert --> VocabInit : ModelRc<VocabularyLessonModel>

VocabInit -> VocabLogic : set_lesson_list(model)

note right of VocabLogic
  ROOT CAUSE (Bug 6.4): the global property was declared
  without an explicit binding —
    in-out property <[VocabularyLessonModel]> lesson-list;
  — so the Slint compiler const-folded it to an empty
  array and never wired it into the reactive dependency
  graph. set_lesson_list() updated the Rust-side value,
  but the `for` loop in LessonStackList kept observing
  the compiled-in empty default (length == 0).

  FIX: give the property an explicit (even trivial)
  binding so the compiler allocates a real reactive slot:
    in-out property <[VocabularyLessonModel]> lesson-list: [];
  This mirrors flashcard-list in FlashcardAppLogic, which
  already has an explicit binding and renders correctly.
end note

VocabLogic -> LessonUI : reactive notification\n(lesson-list changed)
LessonUI -> LessonUI : for lesson[i] in\nVocabularyAppLogic.lesson-list:\n  render LessonStackLabel row
LessonUI --> Main : lesson rows visible\n("N5 Verbs — Eating...", "N5 Verbs — M...", ...)

@enduml
